# Western SRL research sources

When the user asks to find more companies, verify ownership, or expand the directory, use this source priority.

## Tier 1 — Romanian platforms with foreign-ownership filters (start here)

- **Risco.ro** — strongest for bulk discovery; filter by shareholder country (UK, US, etc.), ownership %, turnover, active SRL; Excel export and API.
- **ListaFirme.ro** / **listafirme.eu** — advanced filters for ownership share by nationality, foreign ownership, shareholder name search; good for bulk exports.
- **Termene.ro** — associate/shareholder search, monitoring, API; less direct nationality filters but very comprehensive.

Look for: Foreign Ownership, Shareholders, Advanced Search. Filter: active SRL, country, export when possible.

## Tier 2 — Global depth and UBO chains

- **Orbis (Bureau van Dijk / Moody’s)** — best for corporate trees, UBO, shareholder country of origin; paid/enterprise.
- **Dun & Bradstreet** — secondary global ownership links.
- **OpenCorporates** — free cross-check; incomplete for Romanian shareholder detail.

## Tier 3 — Official verification (per company)

- **ONRC** — portal.onrc.ro; search by name/CUI.
- Order **Certificat Constatator** (~€10–15) for full shareholder list and percentages.
- **Beneficial Owners (UBO) register** — citizenship sometimes available; may require legitimate interest.

Use ONRC to verify candidates found via commercial platforms; not for bulk nationality filtering.

## Tier 4 — Bulk / custom data

- **Clientsolutions.io**, **Lista-firme-romania.ro**, Firme.info, Verifai — bulk lists, new registrations, custom exports (UK/US shareholders above threshold).

## Tier 5 — APIs and automation

- **Termene.ro API**, **Risco.ro API** — automate recurring discovery or integrate into this repo (`scripts/`, `data/`).

## Tier 6 — Supplementary (discovery signals only)

- **LinkedIn Sales Navigator** — owner/founder + UK/US location; not exhaustive.
- **Press/news** — e.g. "British investor Romania SRL", "US owned company Romania".
- **UK Companies House** — trace UK parent/holder of Romanian SRL shares.
- **Romanian law firms / due diligence firms** — custom lists, paid.
- **Data brokers** — custom foreign-owned company lists.

## Default workflow

1. Discover with Risco.ro + ListaFirme.ro (UK/British first, then US, then other Western countries).
2. Deep-check complex structures with Orbis if available.
3. Verify shortlisted SRLs via ONRC Certificat Constatator or registry snippets.
4. Document in `companies/<slug>.md` using existing labels: Likely Western-owned / Western-led, ownership unclear / Verified Western-owned.
5. For each company **and** any non-Romanian parent, also capture: **website**, **social media**, **short sourced history**.
6. Parent companies get their own `parents/<slug>.md` (not indexed in search); link from Romanian SRL profile.
7. Regenerate UI data: `node scripts/build-data.mjs`.

## Parent pages and profile enrichment

- **Romanian SRL profiles** live in `companies/` and appear in the filter UI.
- **Parent / group profiles** live in `parents/` (UK Ltd, GmbH, Oy, etc.). Link from SRL profile; **never** add parents to search index.
- When researching any entity, map:
  - **What it does** — plain-language business activity (products, services, customers)
  - Official website(s)
  - Social media: LinkedIn, Facebook, Instagram, X (only verified URLs from site footer or official profiles)
  - Short history (2–4 bullets, sourced; note uncertainty)
- Apply the same fields to parent pages.
- Standard SRL sections (after Identity): `## What it does`, then `## Size`, then `## Parent / group`, `## Online presence`, `## Short history`.
- Online presence format: Website, LinkedIn, Facebook, Instagram, X — omit lines with no verified URL.

## Project constraints (do not override)

- State nationality only when explicitly sourced; do not infer from company name or branding alone.
- Tag 1–10 employees as **Micro / low-profile** (neutral term).
- BRCC membership and British branding are discovery signals, not proof of ownership.
- Note stale filings and holding-company opacity in rationale.

## Known limitations

- Western owners often use non-resident holding companies; UBO data can be incomplete.
- True exhaustiveness is unlikely without paid bulk exports or APIs.
- Each platform has its own commercial/bulk terms.
